"Step [1]: Click the blank light gray area in the top toolbar region of the Chrome window.\nStep [2]: Type QATAR AIRWAYS into the active Chrome address bar/search field, appending or completing the existing query text there.\nStep [3]: Press Enter to submit the qatar airways search from the Chrome address bar.\nStep [4]: Click the blue \"Qatar Airways Official Website\" search result link.\nStep [5]: Click the \"From\" field in the booking form.\nStep [6]: Click the maroon \"Accept all\" button on the cookie consent banner.\nStep [7]: Click the \"From\" input field in the booking form.\nStep [8]: Type \"SINGAPORE\" into the active \"From\" field.\nStep [9]: Click the autocomplete suggestion \"Singapore, Singapore\" with sublabel \"Singapore Changi Airport\" and code \"SIN\".\nStep [10]: Type \"LOS\" into the active \"To\" destination field.\nStep [11]: Click the autocomplete suggestion \"Los Angeles, United States of America\" with sublabel \"Los Angeles / Tom Bradley International Airport\" and code \"LAX\".\nStep [12]: Click the \"One way\" radio button next to the \"One way\" label.\nStep [13]: Click the departure date field showing \"12 Sep 2025.\"\nStep [14]: Click the September 15 date tile in the calendar, the purple rounded date cell showing \"15\" with fare \"1,453.\"\nStep [15]: Click the maroon \"Continue\" button at the bottom-right of the calendar popup.\nStep [16]: Click the maroon \"Search flights\" button."